Hurricane Maria, which destroyed the whole country 2 years ago.

Juan Anderson turned his bus into a rescue vehicle for people in need during the shock that Maria caused in Dominica.

Juan is from Margate, Florida, the United States. After the impact that Maris caused in Dominica, he decided to return to his country and bought a school bus, which he hoped to use as his own vehicle. But Anton surprised him one night and told him that he was considering returning to Dow.'' Our phone connection was bad, so I needed to use Google Voice to listen to him. I heard Diego talking about the situation in Dominica and when he finished, Anton asked whether he could fund the whole project of putting a school bus into an exclusive vehicle for Dominica.

Juan explained how happy he was about Anton accepting the school bus project.

He said that the bus itself is pretty basic. ”Initially I designed it with a lot of grey spots, a small kitchen, small bedroom, that kind of thing in New York, where I found it. But when Anton saw the bus, he said it was no good and started remaking it. Now the bus has a master bedroom, a kitchen and sink, a shower with indoor and outdoor burners for cooking (to work with propane), a refrigerator, solar panels , solar water heater. All of this only cost about $35,000, which is about 425,000 Dominican Pesos.'' After assembly, the bus looks like a luxury home
